          <td align="left" valign="bottom" width="350" height="30"><p><span class="mark">&diams; </span>Course outline</p>
            <p>"Creating future university image - Let's find out what Nagoya University and its students are like"</p>
            <p>Nagoya University is a large institution with 10,000 undergraduate students, 6,000 graduate students, 1,800 faculty members, and slightly over 1,200 foreign students participating in daily school activities.  University students face the danger of becoming members of a 'lonely crowd' in such a large organization.  What kind of campus life are you leading?  This course specializes on university and study on university students for Nagoya University students, and focuses on considering what students think about and worry about, what the real-life image of Nagoya University is, and how to proceed with studies at the university. </p>
            <p>This course consists of the following four units, each with a specific objective:<br>
            First unit: "How do human beings learn? - From high school to university to members of society"<br>
            Second unit: "What exactly is Nagoya University? - overall image of Nagoya University based on data"<br>
            Third unit: "What are Nagoya University students like? - a focus on their attitudes towards study"<br>
            Fourth unit: "Development of individuality by Nagoya University students - How to develop yourself"</p>
         
            <p><span class="mark">&diams; </span>Course guide</p>
            <p>This course, entitled "How to study at a university - Let's find out what Nagoya University and its students are like," was offered in 2005 (second period on Mondays during the second semester, for all sophomores in all departments). <br>
See <a title="Going Syllabus" href="http://gs.cshe.nagoya-u.ac.jp/">http://gs.cshe.nagoya-u.ac.jp/</a> for further details.</p>
